                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/232.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-14T18:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 14, 1914, 6 pm.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I received information today from Torreon that Villa issued orders that no
                    Spanish property be touched until he personally gave orders. Carranza will
                    probably go to Torreon to see Villa instead of Villa going to Chihuahua as
                    Villa’s presence is necessary at the front.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">G. C. Carothers</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
